WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:26.660 align:middle line:84%
>>It's my pleasure to
introduce you to Dr. John Mack.

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:29.290 align:middle line:84%
Dr. John Mack tells
the Prophets Conference

00:00:29.290 --> 00:00:31.520 align:middle line:84%
a story of one
man's determination

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:35.090 align:middle line:84%
to bear witness to
cosmic mysteries

00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:40.410 align:middle line:84%
with extraordinary implications
for the human future.

00:00:40.410 --> 00:00:42.850 align:middle line:84%
An esteemed professor of
psychiatry at Harvard Medical

00:00:42.850 --> 00:00:46.460 align:middle line:84%
School and a Pulitzer Prize
winning biographer, Professor

00:00:46.460 --> 00:00:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Mack has become an expert
in the controversial study

00:00:51.250 --> 00:00:54.820 align:middle line:84%
of alien abductees
that challenge the most

00:00:54.820 --> 00:00:57.830 align:middle line:84%
basic assumptions that
make up our understanding

00:00:57.830 --> 00:01:03.450 align:middle line:84%
of our existence and our
role in the universe.

00:01:03.450 --> 00:01:08.310 align:middle line:84%
Connections between abductions,
near death experiences,

00:01:08.310 --> 00:01:12.770 align:middle line:84%
and past life regressions
are, Dr. Mack suggests,

00:01:12.770 --> 00:01:17.210 align:middle line:84%
vehicles for recovering
perennial wisdom.

00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:19.848 align:middle line:84%
Let's give a warm
welcome to Dr. John Mack.

00:01:19.848 --> 00:01:20.824 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:01:20.824 --> 00:01:27.110 align:middle line:84%
>>I'm going to give a kind
of statement of the journey

00:01:27.110 --> 00:01:31.360 align:middle line:84%
that I've come to the
place where I arrived

00:01:31.360 --> 00:01:33.290 align:middle line:84%
at the focus of
the title, which is

00:01:33.290 --> 00:01:39.000 align:middle line:84%
the need for a sacred science
that can look at phenomena

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:42.230 align:middle line:84%
such as the so-called
alien abduction

00:01:42.230 --> 00:01:44.740 align:middle line:84%
experience or near
death experiences

00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:47.960 align:middle line:84%
and which can have the
kind of reliability

00:01:47.960 --> 00:01:51.870 align:middle line:84%
that the scientific method
has achieved in relation

00:01:51.870 --> 00:01:53.890 align:middle line:90%
to the physical world.

00:01:53.890 --> 00:01:58.960 align:middle line:84%
I'm indebted to a writer,
an extraordinary scholar

00:01:58.960 --> 00:02:02.800 align:middle line:84%
by the name of Seyyed
Hossein Nasr, who

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.800 align:middle line:84%
has focused on this whole
question of sacred science

00:02:06.800 --> 00:02:08.330 align:middle line:84%
and the need for
a sacred science.

00:02:08.330 --> 00:02:10.720 align:middle line:90%
One of his books has that title.

00:02:10.720 --> 00:02:12.470 align:middle line:90%
He's an Islamic scholar.

00:02:12.470 --> 00:02:14.880 align:middle line:84%
He's at George
Washington University.

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:20.370 align:middle line:84%
And he has been writing
more eloquently than anyone

00:02:20.370 --> 00:02:24.180 align:middle line:84%
I know about the epistemology
of the sacred and the need

00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:28.410 align:middle line:84%
to develop and return
to ways of knowing

00:02:28.410 --> 00:02:33.720 align:middle line:84%
that bring us to a
much more expanded

00:02:33.720 --> 00:02:38.420 align:middle line:84%
profound panoramic
awareness of reality.

00:02:38.420 --> 00:02:41.240 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.240 --> 00:02:44.500 align:middle line:84%
And I'll have a
little bit further

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:49.530 align:middle line:90%
say about him toward the end.

00:02:49.530 --> 00:02:55.670 align:middle line:84%
Now, what happened with me is
that I, as most of you know,

00:02:55.670 --> 00:03:00.670 align:middle line:84%
began about 12 years ago
to work with people who'd

00:03:00.670 --> 00:03:03.700 align:middle line:84%
had these so-called
abduction experiences,

00:03:03.700 --> 00:03:05.980 align:middle line:90%
encounters with strange beings.

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:11.520 align:middle line:84%
And I was at first
incredulous and then astounded

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:15.290 align:middle line:84%
and then excited about
what I was finding.

00:03:15.290 --> 00:03:18.570 align:middle line:84%
I figured if I went out
there and wrote about that

00:03:18.570 --> 00:03:24.240 align:middle line:84%
and talked about that, everybody
who could listen, intelligent

00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:29.750 align:middle line:84%
or not, really, would
find it equally exciting

00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:32.140 align:middle line:84%
and find that this
is really important

00:03:32.140 --> 00:03:34.320 align:middle line:84%
and that we were in a
relationship with beings

00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:36.760 align:middle line:84%
from another dimension
or whatever it was.

00:03:36.760 --> 00:03:40.130 align:middle line:84%
But that wasn't the
response that I received.

00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:43.180 align:middle line:84%
I found a lot of people
got very upset about this

00:03:43.180 --> 00:03:47.670 align:middle line:84%
and began to wonder
why somebody who

00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:51.470 align:middle line:84%
was a more or less
respected Harvard professor

00:03:51.470 --> 00:03:54.900 align:middle line:84%
would embark on such a strange
and disturbing journey, just

00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:58.500 align:middle line:90%
a disturbed journey.

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And the focus we came upon
me and what was wrong with me

00:04:02.110 --> 00:04:04.930 align:middle line:84%
that I should even take
such things seriously.

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:06.750 align:middle line:84%
And of course, in the
psychiatric community

00:04:06.750 --> 00:04:10.940 align:middle line:84%
there's no shortage of
diagnoses for people like me.

00:04:10.940 --> 00:04:12.960 align:middle line:84%
The notion of a
midlife crisis was

00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:19.779 align:middle line:84%
extended into the late '60s,
which I found sort of curiously

00:04:19.779 --> 00:04:21.470 align:middle line:90%
satisfying in a way.

00:04:21.470 --> 00:04:24.010 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:24.010 --> 00:04:30.600 align:middle line:84%
But the fact is this ran into
a kind of buzz saw in the media

00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:32.260 align:middle line:90%
and at Harvard.

00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:37.280 align:middle line:84%
So much so that a committee
was appointed, a three person

00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:39.160 align:middle line:90%
committee, to investigate.

00:04:39.160 --> 00:04:42.580 align:middle line:84%
There were vague hints
of a kind of Kafka

00:04:42.580 --> 00:04:48.360 align:middle line:84%
like nature that questions had
been raised about my methods.

00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:51.540 align:middle line:84%
And I was thoroughly
investigated for 15 months.

00:04:51.540 --> 00:04:58.270 align:middle line:84%
And the dean, when he presented
to me the letter telling me

00:04:58.270 --> 00:05:01.760 align:middle line:84%
that this committee had
been formed, said, "John,

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:04.620 align:middle line:84%
you wouldn't be in,"
because we had been friends,

00:05:04.620 --> 00:05:06.600 align:middle line:84%
"You wouldn't be in
trouble if you had just

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:09.890 align:middle line:84%
said you'd discovered a new
psychiatric syndrome whose

00:05:09.890 --> 00:05:10.790 align:middle line:90%
cause was unknown.

00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:13.950 align:middle line:84%
It's when you said
that this work required

00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:17.010 align:middle line:84%
that perhaps we reconsider
the nature of reality.

00:05:17.010 --> 00:05:20.720 align:middle line:84%
That's what got
you into trouble."

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:23.540 align:middle line:84%
So I've thought
a lot about that.

00:05:23.540 --> 00:05:26.330 align:middle line:84%
One of the recommendations
of the committee

00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:28.950 align:middle line:84%
was that I should
involve more colleagues.

00:05:28.950 --> 00:05:31.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, I had a lot of trouble
doing that in the early years

00:05:31.460 --> 00:05:33.580 align:middle line:84%
because they dismissed
this out of hand

00:05:33.580 --> 00:05:38.280 align:middle line:84%
and wanted to be as far
away from me as possible.

00:05:38.280 --> 00:05:43.800 align:middle line:84%
But finally with the help of
Karen Wosolowski, who's here,

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:48.160 align:middle line:84%
and others in our program, we
had a conference at Harvard.

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:50.834 align:middle line:84%
Not sponsored by Harvard,
but two years ago

00:05:50.834 --> 00:05:53.250 align:middle line:84%
at the Harvard Divinity School,
in which we brought people

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:55.400 align:middle line:84%
together from many
different fields

00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:57.940 align:middle line:84%
to look at how do we think
about, how do we study

00:05:57.940 --> 00:06:02.180 align:middle line:90%
anomalous phenomena like this.

00:06:02.180 --> 00:06:04.810 align:middle line:84%
And what emerged, among many
things, from this meeting

00:06:04.810 --> 00:06:10.340 align:middle line:84%
was that we lacked a reliable
science of human experience.

00:06:10.340 --> 00:06:16.930 align:middle line:84%
And especially of experiences,
however powerful or important,

00:06:16.930 --> 00:06:20.020 align:middle line:84%
that challenged the
prevailing worldview.

00:06:20.020 --> 00:06:23.310 align:middle line:84%
So I've begun to think
about that a great deal.

00:06:23.310 --> 00:06:29.930 align:middle line:90%


00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:35.740 align:middle line:84%
Now, rather than sort of taking
on the scientific method, which

00:06:35.740 --> 00:06:39.090 align:middle line:84%
is pretty popular
these days, I've

00:06:39.090 --> 00:06:43.350 align:middle line:84%
been more interested in what
is an offer that has been

00:06:43.350 --> 00:06:44.796 align:middle line:90%
so extraordinarily successful?

00:06:44.796 --> 00:06:47.900 align:middle line:90%


00:06:47.900 --> 00:06:50.460 align:middle line:84%
A friend of mine, Bill
Gibson's a playwright

00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:54.009 align:middle line:84%
who wrote "Two For The
Seesaw" and "Miracle Workers"

00:06:54.009 --> 00:06:54.550 align:middle line:90%
and a friend.

00:06:54.550 --> 00:06:58.600 align:middle line:84%
And he was raised as a Roman
Catholic and very quite strict.

00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:01.580 align:middle line:84%
And he sort of left that,
became very secular.

00:07:01.580 --> 00:07:03.670 align:middle line:84%
And then he kind of
wandered back occasionally

00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:05.540 align:middle line:90%
into the church.

00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:08.900 align:middle line:84%
And he said when he goes into
the church, he told me this,

00:07:08.900 --> 00:07:12.590 align:middle line:84%
when he goes into the
church, his consciousness

00:07:12.590 --> 00:07:17.700 align:middle line:84%
seems to open up and he feels
connected with the divine,

00:07:17.700 --> 00:07:22.280 align:middle line:84%
with beings that extend
beyond this world.

00:07:22.280 --> 00:07:24.710 align:middle line:84%
And it's an
incredible experience.

00:07:24.710 --> 00:07:27.560 align:middle line:84%
And then when he comes
out of the church,

00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:31.010 align:middle line:84%
he goes back to saying this
is reality, the material

00:07:31.010 --> 00:07:33.530 align:middle line:84%
world around me, and
he dismisses all that.

00:07:33.530 --> 00:07:35.610 align:middle line:84%
So I asked him, I
said, "Well Bill,

00:07:35.610 --> 00:07:41.360 align:middle line:84%
why you favor of the
worldview that you return

00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:43.910 align:middle line:84%
to when you come out of
the church over the one

00:07:43.910 --> 00:07:46.460 align:middle line:84%
that you experience
in the church?"

00:07:46.460 --> 00:07:54.390 align:middle line:84%
And he said that science, the
material science, Newtonian,

00:07:54.390 --> 00:07:57.140 align:middle line:84%
Cartesian science, wherever
you want to call it,

00:07:57.140 --> 00:08:00.670 align:middle line:84%
has been so successful
in giving us

00:08:00.670 --> 00:08:03.412 align:middle line:90%
a blueprint, a map of the world.

00:08:03.412 --> 00:08:04.870 align:middle line:84%
And so I argued
with him of course,

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:05.880 align:middle line:84%
and I said, well what
about all these other

00:08:05.880 --> 00:08:06.600 align:middle line:84%
the dimensions
and this and that.

00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:08.600 align:middle line:84%
He said, but there's
no reliable way

00:08:08.600 --> 00:08:10.900 align:middle line:84%
of knowing what's true in
those other dimensions.

00:08:10.900 --> 00:08:13.030 align:middle line:90%
Anything seems to go.

00:08:13.030 --> 00:08:14.540 align:middle line:90%
So I thought about that.

00:08:14.540 --> 00:08:17.270 align:middle line:90%


00:08:17.270 --> 00:08:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And I begin to think about, how
do we decide when somebody's

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:27.190 align:middle line:84%
reporting to us, profound,
powerful human experiences,

00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:30.790 align:middle line:84%
or potentially so, how do
we decide what to believe?

00:08:30.790 --> 00:08:34.559 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the reasons that
channeling is such a problem.

00:08:34.559 --> 00:08:37.679 align:middle line:84%
Some channeled information
is tremendously important

00:08:37.679 --> 00:08:39.659 align:middle line:84%
and the channelers people
of great integrity.

00:08:39.659 --> 00:08:43.730 align:middle line:84%
But anybody can sort
of hang on a shingle

00:08:43.730 --> 00:08:46.600 align:middle line:84%
and say they're channeling this
or that entity or god figure.

00:08:46.600 --> 00:08:50.006 align:middle line:84%
And the universe is just
as full of misinformation

00:08:50.006 --> 00:08:51.380 align:middle line:84%
out there as it
is in Washington.

00:08:51.380 --> 00:08:54.560 align:middle line:90%


00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:57.475 align:middle line:84%
So that question
began to really,

00:08:57.475 --> 00:08:59.650 align:middle line:84%
I began to wrestle
with that a lot.

00:08:59.650 --> 00:09:04.040 align:middle line:90%


00:09:04.040 --> 00:09:08.370 align:middle line:84%
It's also, as for example in
the so-called alien abduction

00:09:08.370 --> 00:09:11.670 align:middle line:84%
matter, the stakes
are very high.

00:09:11.670 --> 00:09:13.220 align:middle line:84%
We're dealing with
something which

00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:17.250 align:middle line:84%
so fundamentally challenges
the Western worldview.

00:09:17.250 --> 00:09:22.040 align:middle line:84%
As those of us that claim to
be or offering information

00:09:22.040 --> 00:09:25.370 align:middle line:84%
might do that are being held
to very tough standards.

00:09:25.370 --> 00:09:28.240 align:middle line:84%
And properly so, because the
scientific method, whatever

00:09:28.240 --> 00:09:31.490 align:middle line:84%
its limitations has
been, has developed

00:09:31.490 --> 00:09:34.310 align:middle line:84%
very clear standards
of experimentation,

00:09:34.310 --> 00:09:37.652 align:middle line:84%
testing, rational analysis,
replicability, and so forth.

00:09:37.652 --> 00:09:38.610 align:middle line:90%
And we don't have that.

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:39.990 align:middle line:90%
And we can't have that.

00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:41.080 align:middle line:90%
But what can we have?

00:09:41.080 --> 00:09:43.640 align:middle line:90%


00:09:43.640 --> 00:09:48.510 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're dependent
on the reports.

00:09:48.510 --> 00:09:49.170 align:middle line:90%
Not entirely.

00:09:49.170 --> 00:09:52.240 align:middle line:90%
There is physical evidence.

00:09:52.240 --> 00:09:56.970 align:middle line:84%
For example, abductees do
have marks on their bodies.

00:09:56.970 --> 00:10:01.430 align:middle line:84%
There's missing time, although
it's hard to objectify that.

00:10:01.430 --> 00:10:02.940 align:middle line:84%
But the physical
evidence is kind

00:10:02.940 --> 00:10:08.400 align:middle line:84%
of like if you were trying to
study a giant and all that you

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:11.800 align:middle line:84%
got was the toenail
of the giant.

00:10:11.800 --> 00:10:13.812 align:middle line:84%
I even like the image of
it because it's sort of

00:10:13.812 --> 00:10:16.420 align:middle line:90%
curved like a spaceship.

00:10:16.420 --> 00:10:19.120 align:middle line:90%
And you study that toenail.

00:10:19.120 --> 00:10:21.870 align:middle line:84%
You measure it and you get how
many toenails have you seen

00:10:21.870 --> 00:10:23.828 align:middle line:84%
or how many people have
seen it, this and that.

00:10:23.828 --> 00:10:26.610 align:middle line:84%
And you conclude this
is what it's about.

00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:28.080 align:middle line:90%
But you don't see the toe.

00:10:28.080 --> 00:10:29.540 align:middle line:84%
You don't see the
rest of the body.

00:10:29.540 --> 00:10:32.710 align:middle line:84%
You don't see the
giant that's there.

00:10:32.710 --> 00:10:34.040 align:middle line:90%
You miss knowing.

00:10:34.040 --> 00:10:37.290 align:middle line:84%
But how do you know the
giant of the reality beyond?

00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:40.400 align:middle line:84%
You know through consciousness,
through your whole self.

00:10:40.400 --> 00:10:42.621 align:middle line:84%
But how do you know
what's reliable?

00:10:42.621 --> 00:10:44.120 align:middle line:84%
And I don't have
the answer to this.

00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:48.950 align:middle line:84%
I just can keep asking this
question and addressing it.

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:53.590 align:middle line:84%
In part it's a clinical
question because it

00:10:53.590 --> 00:10:56.910 align:middle line:84%
involves the reliability
of the people who

00:10:56.910 --> 00:10:58.832 align:middle line:90%
are making the reports.

00:10:58.832 --> 00:11:00.290 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things it allowed me

00:11:00.290 --> 00:11:03.680 align:middle line:84%
to endure through this whole
Harvard inquisition period

00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:07.440 align:middle line:84%
was that I could keep saying,
look, you see these people.

00:11:07.440 --> 00:11:08.170 align:middle line:90%
You talk to them.

00:11:08.170 --> 00:11:10.510 align:middle line:84%
Do they seem like
they're suffering

00:11:10.510 --> 00:11:12.225 align:middle line:84%
from some kind of
mental condition?

00:11:12.225 --> 00:11:14.832 align:middle line:90%


00:11:14.832 --> 00:11:16.540 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes people just
refuse to see them.

00:11:16.540 --> 00:11:19.669 align:middle line:84%
But those who were willing
to come in the room with me

00:11:19.669 --> 00:11:21.460 align:middle line:84%
would come out shaking
their heads and say,

00:11:21.460 --> 00:11:22.293 align:middle line:90%
I see what you mean.

00:11:22.293 --> 00:11:24.090 align:middle line:90%
I don't understand this either.

00:11:24.090 --> 00:11:26.675 align:middle line:84%
And I keep saying,
nothing in my 40,

00:11:26.675 --> 00:11:29.700 align:middle line:84%
of course it's now more
than 40, years of experience

00:11:29.700 --> 00:11:33.950 align:middle line:84%
as a clinician has given me
one bit of information that

00:11:33.950 --> 00:11:39.560 align:middle line:84%
helps me understand what
I'm hearing psychiatrically.

00:11:39.560 --> 00:11:43.430 align:middle line:84%
The people are talking
to me about experiences

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:46.350 align:middle line:84%
with emotion that's appropriate
to what they're talking about,

00:11:46.350 --> 00:11:47.810 align:middle line:90%
appropriate questioning.

00:11:47.810 --> 00:11:49.410 align:middle line:90%
They have solid lives otherwise.

00:11:49.410 --> 00:11:51.370 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing to
suggest delusion.

00:11:51.370 --> 00:11:54.674 align:middle line:84%
The only problem,
the only problem

00:11:54.674 --> 00:11:56.090 align:middle line:84%
is that what they're
talking about

00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:59.880 align:middle line:84%
is not considered possible
from the standpoint

00:11:59.880 --> 00:12:03.830 align:middle line:84%
of the worldview in which
they and I were raised.

00:12:03.830 --> 00:12:06.580 align:middle line:84%
Now, I happen to make
the choice of deciding

00:12:06.580 --> 00:12:08.480 align:middle line:84%
that it's something
wrong with the worldview

00:12:08.480 --> 00:12:12.640 align:middle line:84%
rather than that if would just
keep going down that same road,

00:12:12.640 --> 00:12:15.560 align:middle line:84%
we're going to find a syndrome
that's going to explain this.

00:12:15.560 --> 00:12:18.650 align:middle line:84%
But once you go down the road
of challenging the worldview,

00:12:18.650 --> 00:12:22.260 align:middle line:84%
things really begin
to get interesting.

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:26.030 align:middle line:84%
The people's stories were
consistent one from another.

00:12:26.030 --> 00:12:27.180 align:middle line:90%
They would vary some.

00:12:27.180 --> 00:12:29.840 align:middle line:90%
Some were more traumatic.

00:12:29.840 --> 00:12:34.710 align:middle line:84%
Some were more opening up to
experiences of the divine.

00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:36.680 align:middle line:84%
But by and large there
was a consistent pattern

00:12:36.680 --> 00:12:38.250 align:middle line:90%
of the stories.

00:12:38.250 --> 00:12:40.900 align:middle line:84%
And they were
reported with feeling

00:12:40.900 --> 00:12:49.360 align:middle line:84%
that I could determine
was based on what

00:12:49.360 --> 00:12:51.920 align:middle line:84%
sounded like something that
had really happened to them.

00:12:51.920 --> 00:12:56.740 align:middle line:84%
And the intensity of the
feeling, as I mentioned,

00:12:56.740 --> 00:13:00.660 align:middle line:84%
the self-doubt, the clinical
soundness of these individuals.

00:13:00.660 --> 00:13:03.790 align:middle line:90%
All of this I could speak about.

00:13:03.790 --> 00:13:06.740 align:middle line:90%
But there was something more.

00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:09.940 align:middle line:84%
Because even that, I'd say,
look, I argued, I presented,

00:13:09.940 --> 00:13:11.700 align:middle line:84%
everybody do
psychological tests.

00:13:11.700 --> 00:13:14.860 align:middle line:84%
You find out that there's no
pathology that can explain it.

00:13:14.860 --> 00:13:19.370 align:middle line:84%
We have done studies that
appear of that nature.

00:13:19.370 --> 00:13:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And psychiatric
analyses don't reveal

00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:24.950 align:middle line:84%
anything that's
particularly helpful

00:13:24.950 --> 00:13:28.460 align:middle line:90%
or doesn't add anything to it.

00:13:28.460 --> 00:13:30.977 align:middle line:84%
But even those arguments
don't get anywhere

00:13:30.977 --> 00:13:32.560 align:middle line:84%
or don't get very
far, because there's

00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:37.390 align:middle line:84%
something missing in this
question of what is reliable.

00:13:37.390 --> 00:13:42.180 align:middle line:84%
And I came upon the
notion of the witness.

00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:47.570 align:middle line:84%
Now, this came because in
San Marino in April 1999,

00:13:47.570 --> 00:13:49.160 align:middle line:90%
I was at a conference.

00:13:49.160 --> 00:13:54.820 align:middle line:84%
And at that conference was
a Catholic prelate wearing

00:13:54.820 --> 00:13:56.210 align:middle line:90%
the cassock.

00:13:56.210 --> 00:14:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And he was talking about the
UFO and abduction phenomenon.

00:14:02.690 --> 00:14:06.010 align:middle line:84%
And he said, and he was not
speaking for the Vatican,

00:14:06.010 --> 00:14:09.120 align:middle line:84%
but clearly what he said was
not offensive to the Vatican,

00:14:09.120 --> 00:14:13.070 align:middle line:84%
he said, "I take this
very, very seriously why?

00:14:13.070 --> 00:14:16.950 align:middle line:84%
Because there are so
many reliable witnesses,

00:14:16.950 --> 00:14:19.520 align:middle line:90%
apparently reliable witnesses.

00:14:19.520 --> 00:14:22.080 align:middle line:84%
And in the church
when we're trying

00:14:22.080 --> 00:14:26.600 align:middle line:84%
to evaluate miracles, determine
what miracles to believe,

00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:30.020 align:middle line:90%
we have to depend on witnesses."

00:14:30.020 --> 00:14:31.460 align:middle line:90%
Now, what is a reliable witness?

00:14:31.460 --> 00:14:35.370 align:middle line:84%
Well, they go through
much of what we do.

00:14:35.370 --> 00:14:38.280 align:middle line:84%
Currently they've been using
psychiatric and psychological

00:14:38.280 --> 00:14:40.450 align:middle line:84%
examinations of people
reporting miracles.

00:14:40.450 --> 00:14:45.640 align:middle line:84%
But there is something about
the Witness with a capital W

00:14:45.640 --> 00:14:49.597 align:middle line:90%
that is in a sacred tradition.

00:14:49.597 --> 00:14:50.930 align:middle line:90%
Not just in the Catholic Church.

00:14:50.930 --> 00:14:53.310 align:middle line:84%
I talked with a zen
master about this.

00:14:53.310 --> 00:14:57.120 align:middle line:84%
He says that there's a
way that you experience

00:14:57.120 --> 00:15:01.800 align:middle line:84%
somebody who has
a clarity of mind,

00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:03.682 align:middle line:84%
does not have another
agenda, is not attached

00:15:03.682 --> 00:15:04.640 align:middle line:90%
to what they're saying.

00:15:04.640 --> 00:15:06.550 align:middle line:84%
There's a purity of the
way they express it.

00:15:06.550 --> 00:15:09.556 align:middle line:84%
You experience what they're
talking about as if it

00:15:09.556 --> 00:15:10.680 align:middle line:90%
were happening to yourself.

00:15:10.680 --> 00:15:13.620 align:middle line:84%
They convey to you
something that you just

00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:16.040 align:middle line:90%
are part of the experience.

00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:18.620 align:middle line:84%
And one of the people that
I work with, an experiencer,

00:15:18.620 --> 00:15:24.090 align:middle line:84%
said it's as if they come and
they've been touched by God.

00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:27.700 align:middle line:84%
You feel that there's
that connection that they

00:15:27.700 --> 00:15:31.190 align:middle line:90%
express and represent.

00:15:31.190 --> 00:15:36.410 align:middle line:84%
So I began then to
reinterpret my own job.

00:15:36.410 --> 00:15:39.390 align:middle line:84%
Since I'm not a direct
witness in the sense of having

00:15:39.390 --> 00:15:43.750 align:middle line:84%
had these experiences
with beings or been taken

00:15:43.750 --> 00:15:45.600 align:middle line:84%
or whatever happens
to people when

00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:49.320 align:middle line:90%
they encounter this phenomenon.

00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:53.300 align:middle line:84%
I began to look upon
myself as a kind of witness

00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:56.540 align:middle line:84%
to the witnesses, somebody
that helps give them voice

00:15:56.540 --> 00:15:58.530 align:middle line:90%
or asserts their reliability.

00:15:58.530 --> 00:16:05.870 align:middle line:84%
Because the notion of somebody
in my "position," quote,

00:16:05.870 --> 00:16:11.250 align:middle line:84%
unquote, and that's in
an archetypal sense,

00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:13.570 align:middle line:84%
has a chance, even
though it gets shot

00:16:13.570 --> 00:16:16.680 align:middle line:84%
at a lot, a chance to
be heard or to enable

00:16:16.680 --> 00:16:17.740 align:middle line:90%
other people to be heard.

00:16:17.740 --> 00:16:20.950 align:middle line:84%
So there is this relationship I
have with the experiences where

00:16:20.950 --> 00:16:24.580 align:middle line:84%
I am helping them
to be legitimized

00:16:24.580 --> 00:16:26.460 align:middle line:90%
because I'm convinced.

00:16:26.460 --> 00:16:30.169 align:middle line:84%
It's not just to help them
integrate their experiences.

00:16:30.169 --> 00:16:31.460 align:middle line:90%
And that's important in itself.

00:16:31.460 --> 00:16:34.180 align:middle line:84%
But I believe they
bring something

00:16:34.180 --> 00:16:36.115 align:middle line:84%
of extraordinary
importance to the culture.

00:16:36.115 --> 00:16:40.510 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they are
receiving information

00:16:40.510 --> 00:16:44.500 align:middle line:84%
from whatever source
this phenomenon emanates

00:16:44.500 --> 00:16:50.240 align:middle line:84%
from that says human
beings have to change.

00:16:50.240 --> 00:16:52.050 align:middle line:84%
We have to open
our consciousness.

00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:55.400 align:middle line:84%
We're acting like, as one of
the experiencers would call it,

00:16:55.400 --> 00:16:56.720 align:middle line:90%
rednecks in the galaxy.

00:16:56.720 --> 00:16:59.850 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:59.850 --> 00:17:01.860 align:middle line:84%
Bent on destroying
not only ourselves,

00:17:01.860 --> 00:17:05.819 align:middle line:84%
but life way beyond ourselves,
other species on the planet,

00:17:05.819 --> 00:17:10.630 align:middle line:84%
and even causing a cosmic
ripple in the dimensions

00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:11.700 align:middle line:90%
of our destructiveness.

00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:12.849 align:middle line:90%
They have to change.

00:17:12.849 --> 00:17:14.500 align:middle line:84%
And the experiencers
have something

00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:17.550 align:middle line:84%
terribly important to
tell us about this.

00:17:17.550 --> 00:17:20.250 align:middle line:84%
But then those of us
that work with them

00:17:20.250 --> 00:17:24.844 align:middle line:84%
have that job of legitimizing,
trying to legitimize

00:17:24.844 --> 00:17:25.760 align:middle line:90%
what they have to say.

00:17:25.760 --> 00:17:31.790 align:middle line:84%
Now, Veronica who I've
not known very long.

00:17:31.790 --> 00:17:37.030 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the first time that
Veronica and I were ever

00:17:37.030 --> 00:17:39.665 align:middle line:84%
in a conference together,
I spontaneously, I

00:17:39.665 --> 00:17:41.540 align:middle line:84%
