was a lot of traffic on
the road up and down.

00:25:17.110 --> 00:25:19.280 align:middle line:84%
So we got near the top
and it was already dark.

00:25:19.280 --> 00:25:21.900 align:middle line:84%
And so we said, well,
let's just get off

00:25:21.900 --> 00:25:25.930 align:middle line:90%
of this view parking lot thing.

00:25:25.930 --> 00:25:31.870 align:middle line:84%
And so we parked the
car and we looked out

00:25:31.870 --> 00:25:37.210 align:middle line:84%
from the mountain down towards
the town, the lights below.

00:25:37.210 --> 00:25:40.530 align:middle line:84%
But it was so cold and
windy that we said, well,

00:25:40.530 --> 00:25:43.532 align:middle line:84%
don't let's hang around
and we'll go back down.

00:25:43.532 --> 00:25:49.500 align:middle line:84%
At which point my companion
turned back towards the car

00:25:49.500 --> 00:25:55.470 align:middle line:84%
and he suddenly
noticed this what

00:25:55.470 --> 00:26:02.855 align:middle line:84%
seemed like a stationary object
off the side of the mountain.

00:26:02.855 --> 00:26:06.350 align:middle line:90%


00:26:06.350 --> 00:26:10.540 align:middle line:84%
And it had these
circulating colored lights

00:26:10.540 --> 00:26:12.880 align:middle line:90%
on its underbelly.

00:26:12.880 --> 00:26:16.140 align:middle line:84%
And that was really only
the part that we could see.

00:26:16.140 --> 00:26:21.670 align:middle line:84%
So I don't really know what the
shape of whatever this was was.

00:26:21.670 --> 00:26:24.490 align:middle line:84%
But he saw him and he said,
looking at it like this,

00:26:24.490 --> 00:26:28.580 align:middle line:84%
he said, well, what
do you think that is?

00:26:28.580 --> 00:26:33.670 align:middle line:84%
So I followed his gaze and I
turned to where he was looking.

00:26:33.670 --> 00:26:41.790 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, an
extraordinary thing happened.

00:26:41.790 --> 00:26:46.200 align:middle line:84%
The whole landscape
suddenly shifted

00:26:46.200 --> 00:26:50.890 align:middle line:84%
into a completely
different dimension.

00:26:50.890 --> 00:26:52.650 align:middle line:84%
That's the only way
I can describe it.

00:26:52.650 --> 00:26:55.400 align:middle line:90%


00:26:55.400 --> 00:27:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Our feet were still planted
on the same geographical spot.

00:27:01.380 --> 00:27:04.200 align:middle line:84%
But the wind
completely disappeared

00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:08.860 align:middle line:84%
and the entire traffic
completely disappeared.

00:27:08.860 --> 00:27:12.900 align:middle line:84%
What happened was
the landscape became

00:27:12.900 --> 00:27:16.180 align:middle line:90%
illumined by a sort of moon.

00:27:16.180 --> 00:27:20.190 align:middle line:84%
If I were to try to describe
it, it was a kind of moonscape,

00:27:20.190 --> 00:27:25.550 align:middle line:84%
as if a light source you didn't
know illuminated the land

00:27:25.550 --> 00:27:28.360 align:middle line:90%
that we were on.

00:27:28.360 --> 00:27:34.810 align:middle line:84%
But as I say, it was moved into
a profound kind of stillness.

00:27:34.810 --> 00:27:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And the wind and traffic
were no longer present.

00:27:42.580 --> 00:27:47.360 align:middle line:84%
There was this union of the
timeless with the time bound.

00:27:47.360 --> 00:27:49.830 align:middle line:84%
As if fully knowledgeable
of my own presence,

00:27:49.830 --> 00:27:53.470 align:middle line:84%
but in communion
with something that

00:27:53.470 --> 00:27:56.660 align:middle line:90%
was eternal and transcendent.

00:27:56.660 --> 00:27:59.480 align:middle line:90%


00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:08.080 align:middle line:84%
The other feeling
was one of a kind

00:28:08.080 --> 00:28:13.470 align:middle line:84%
of benign, compassionate,
loving presence.

00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:18.530 align:middle line:90%


00:28:18.530 --> 00:28:23.990 align:middle line:84%
I think we are being called
increasingly to the center that

00:28:23.990 --> 00:28:24.565 align:middle line:90%
is the heart.

00:28:24.565 --> 00:28:29.070 align:middle line:90%


00:28:29.070 --> 00:28:34.434 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how
long that event took.

00:28:34.434 --> 00:28:35.850 align:middle line:84%
When I say to
people I don't know,

00:28:35.850 --> 00:28:38.010 align:middle line:84%
I can only say it seemed
like about two minutes.

00:28:38.010 --> 00:28:42.800 align:middle line:84%
Even that may be
longer than it was.

00:28:42.800 --> 00:28:51.080 align:middle line:84%
But when that window,
whatever it was, closed,

00:28:51.080 --> 00:28:53.910 align:middle line:84%
the wind came back
with full force

00:28:53.910 --> 00:28:56.066 align:middle line:84%
and the traffic was
again on the road

00:28:56.066 --> 00:28:57.190 align:middle line:90%
going up and down the road.

00:28:57.190 --> 00:29:01.230 align:middle line:90%


00:29:01.230 --> 00:29:04.775 align:middle line:84%
It was an extraordinarily
awesome experiences.

00:29:04.775 --> 00:29:08.070 align:middle line:84%
That's the only way
I know how to say it.

00:29:08.070 --> 00:29:11.080 align:middle line:84%
We got back in the car
and we drove down and back

00:29:11.080 --> 00:29:15.150 align:middle line:84%
to the house that
we were guests in.

00:29:15.150 --> 00:29:19.790 align:middle line:90%
And two things about that.

00:29:19.790 --> 00:29:25.180 align:middle line:84%
One, everybody was
in bed and asleep.

00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:27.874 align:middle line:90%
It was 2 o'clock in the morning.

00:29:27.874 --> 00:29:29.290 align:middle line:84%
I didn't realize
that at the time.

00:29:29.290 --> 00:29:31.040 align:middle line:84%
It was actually only
later that I suddenly

00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:35.470 align:middle line:84%
realized, well, what happened
between about nine and two?

00:29:35.470 --> 00:29:38.860 align:middle line:84%
The other thing was that
when I went into the bathroom

00:29:38.860 --> 00:29:42.900 align:middle line:84%
and looked in the mirror,
I had light radiating off

00:29:42.900 --> 00:29:48.560 align:middle line:84%
a rainbow kind of aura
radiating off my form.

00:29:48.560 --> 00:29:51.660 align:middle line:90%


00:29:51.660 --> 00:29:53.620 align:middle line:84%
When I went back
to the East Coast,

00:29:53.620 --> 00:29:58.530 align:middle line:84%
I didn't tell a couple of
people about this experience.

00:29:58.530 --> 00:30:01.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry to say that I've been
a Jungian therapist for about

00:30:01.300 --> 00:30:06.220 align:middle line:84%
20 years and have worked
a lot with dreams.

00:30:06.220 --> 00:30:09.201 align:middle line:84%
It's almost impossible, I hope
I'm not offending anybody here.

00:30:09.201 --> 00:30:10.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure there are exceptions.

00:30:10.450 --> 00:30:14.740 align:middle line:84%
But what was sad to me was
that this experience could not

00:30:14.740 --> 00:30:17.180 align:middle line:84%
be valued for the actual
ontological reality

00:30:17.180 --> 00:30:18.640 align:middle line:90%
that it had.

00:30:18.640 --> 00:30:21.760 align:middle line:84%
In other words, if I'd reported
this experience as a dream,

00:30:21.760 --> 00:30:24.340 align:middle line:84%
it would have been
much more acceptable.

00:30:24.340 --> 00:30:28.040 align:middle line:84%
Because with dreams, particular
in the Jungian tradition,

00:30:28.040 --> 00:30:32.585 align:middle line:84%
you appreciate dreams for
their symbolic as if resonance.

00:30:32.585 --> 00:30:37.040 align:middle line:90%


00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:39.960 align:middle line:84%
But it's as if it's not OK to
have a really real experience,

00:30:39.960 --> 00:30:44.275 align:middle line:84%
even though these experiences
are not of the ordinary world.

00:30:44.275 --> 00:30:47.290 align:middle line:90%


00:30:47.290 --> 00:30:49.760 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, they're
not interior experiences.

00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:51.560 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
that's happening inside.

00:30:51.560 --> 00:30:55.780 align:middle line:84%
It is actually a movement
to a new outside,

00:30:55.780 --> 00:31:01.170 align:middle line:84%
but the outside is not
that of ordinary reality.

00:31:01.170 --> 00:31:03.760 align:middle line:84%
Like John, I feel
that there's a kind

00:31:03.760 --> 00:31:14.280 align:middle line:84%
of perennial ancient mystic,
gnostic, alchemical gnosis that

00:31:14.280 --> 00:31:19.320 align:middle line:84%
before our time, our time being
the last 400 or 500 years,

00:31:19.320 --> 00:31:23.710 align:middle line:84%
knew these states of being
and highly valued them.

00:31:23.710 --> 00:31:26.070 align:middle line:84%
For example, in
the Sufi tradition

00:31:26.070 --> 00:31:28.050 align:middle line:84%
it's called the
mundus imaginalis.

00:31:28.050 --> 00:31:31.550 align:middle line:84%
A third ontological
realm between pure spirit

00:31:31.550 --> 00:31:33.370 align:middle line:90%
and the sensory world.

00:31:33.370 --> 00:31:37.035 align:middle line:84%
And in alchemy, of course,
it has other names too.

00:31:37.035 --> 00:31:39.450 align:middle line:90%
The imaginatio verit.

00:31:39.450 --> 00:31:41.360 align:middle line:84%
And that was distinguished
from fantasy.

00:31:41.360 --> 00:31:46.280 align:middle line:84%
It was a world that was in
between matter and spirit,

00:31:46.280 --> 00:31:49.650 align:middle line:84%
a subtle body realm but
they are constructed

00:31:49.650 --> 00:31:54.140 align:middle line:84%
by unconditional
cosmic compassion.

00:31:54.140 --> 00:32:00.380 align:middle line:84%
And the other is that
they're landscapes

00:32:00.380 --> 00:32:01.980 align:middle line:90%
of tremendous beauty.

00:32:01.980 --> 00:32:04.450 align:middle line:84%
Beauty being also a value
that we have lost, I think,

00:32:04.450 --> 00:32:07.160 align:middle line:90%
in our time.

00:32:07.160 --> 00:32:15.040 align:middle line:84%
And they carry enormous
emotional and healing powers.

00:32:15.040 --> 00:32:19.510 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I think is
being recovered in our time.

00:32:19.510 --> 00:32:20.566 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:32:20.566 --> 00:32:23.542 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:32:23.542 --> 00:32:29.000 align:middle line:90%


00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:32.630 align:middle line:84%
>>I wanted to mention something
that's coming up in my work

00:32:32.630 --> 00:32:39.410 align:middle line:84%
now, which is the
sort of frontier edge.

00:32:39.410 --> 00:32:43.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm reading about
and seeing in my work

00:32:43.300 --> 00:32:45.130 align:middle line:84%
people that are
having experiences

00:32:45.130 --> 00:32:48.640 align:middle line:90%
with so-called reptilian beings.

00:32:48.640 --> 00:32:54.900 align:middle line:84%
And these experiences vary
from sexual encounters

00:32:54.900 --> 00:33:01.190 align:middle line:84%
to violent encounters
even to people

00:33:01.190 --> 00:33:04.190 align:middle line:90%
being devoured by these beings.

00:33:04.190 --> 00:33:07.880 align:middle line:84%
But whatever the experiences
are, they are powerful

00:33:07.880 --> 00:33:11.640 align:middle line:84%
and they are primal
and they are very real.

00:33:11.640 --> 00:33:21.130 align:middle line:84%
And it occurred to me while
I was thinking about this,

00:33:21.130 --> 00:33:26.540 align:middle line:84%
the original or first epic
in the English language

00:33:26.540 --> 00:33:28.600 align:middle line:90%
was "Beowulf."

00:33:28.600 --> 00:33:33.330 align:middle line:84%
And what "Beowulf" is
about, if you recall,

00:33:33.330 --> 00:33:37.860 align:middle line:84%
is the heroic figure
there wrestles

00:33:37.860 --> 00:33:40.780 align:middle line:84%
with a dragon by
the name of Grendel

00:33:40.780 --> 00:33:45.410 align:middle line:84%
and later with his mother,
which hardly needs interpreting.

00:33:45.410 --> 00:33:50.240 align:middle line:90%
And he drowns in the water.

00:33:50.240 --> 00:33:53.460 align:middle line:84%
The son, Grendel, he
just crunches and crushes

00:33:53.460 --> 00:33:56.480 align:middle line:90%
in a great battle.

00:33:56.480 --> 00:33:58.820 align:middle line:84%
It made me think what
connection there might be.

00:33:58.820 --> 00:34:00.360 align:middle line:90%
And this is speculative.

00:34:00.360 --> 00:34:02.640 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't do this
anyplace but here.

00:34:02.640 --> 00:34:06.770 align:middle line:84%
But what connection
is there with the fact

00:34:06.770 --> 00:34:11.909 align:middle line:84%
that our first epic is a battle
between a reptilian dragon

00:34:11.909 --> 00:34:17.110 align:middle line:90%
being and a heroic human?

00:34:17.110 --> 00:34:19.270 align:middle line:84%
And to me those battles
are very similar to what

00:34:19.270 --> 00:34:22.860 align:middle line:84%
I hear about in the whole
reptilian struggle of some

00:34:22.860 --> 00:34:25.210 align:middle line:90%
of the abduction experiences.

00:34:25.210 --> 00:34:27.580 align:middle line:84%
So I thought two
things about this.

00:34:27.580 --> 00:34:31.560 align:middle line:84%
One is there's some aspect
of our own primal reptilian

00:34:31.560 --> 00:34:36.170 align:middle line:84%
phylogenetically carried
nature that we have not

00:34:36.170 --> 00:34:37.090 align:middle line:90%
come to terms with.

00:34:37.090 --> 00:34:39.280 align:middle line:84%
And right in that
first epic, we're

00:34:39.280 --> 00:34:41.909 align:middle line:84%
projecting it
outside of ourselves

00:34:41.909 --> 00:34:43.820 align:middle line:90%
and then destroying it.

00:34:43.820 --> 00:34:47.239 align:middle line:84%
So there's sort of a more
somewhat standard return

00:34:47.239 --> 00:34:50.250 align:middle line:84%
of the repressed phenomenon
there to be integrated

00:34:50.250 --> 00:34:52.170 align:middle line:90%
and dealt with.

00:34:52.170 --> 00:34:54.460 align:middle line:90%
But that doesn't quite do it.

00:34:54.460 --> 00:34:56.719 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's important
and that's part of it.

00:34:56.719 --> 00:35:01.065 align:middle line:84%
But the other part of it is
that these beings are not simply

00:35:01.065 --> 00:35:01.565 align:middle line:90%
projections.

00:35:01.565 --> 00:35:05.340 align:middle line:84%
In other words, we have
this anthropocentric notion

00:35:05.340 --> 00:35:08.240 align:middle line:84%
coming down through
psychology and psychiatry

00:35:08.240 --> 00:35:11.420 align:middle line:84%
that these mythic
entities are simply

00:35:11.420 --> 00:35:13.360 align:middle line:84%
projections of our
own unconscious,

00:35:13.360 --> 00:35:14.820 align:middle line:90%
mythic or otherwise.

00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:18.630 align:middle line:84%
And we don't credit the fact
that the universe may actually

00:35:18.630 --> 00:35:22.230 align:middle line:84%
contain beings of this
kind that reach us

00:35:22.230 --> 00:35:23.300 align:middle line:90%
from another dimension.

00:35:23.300 --> 00:35:27.210 align:middle line:84%
That's more disturbing
to our world view.

00:35:27.210 --> 00:35:31.300 align:middle line:84%
But I think the last
thing about that

00:35:31.300 --> 00:35:33.550 align:middle line:84%
that came up just
a few days ago when

00:35:33.550 --> 00:35:36.780 align:middle line:84%
I was working with a woman
who was having reptilian

00:35:36.780 --> 00:35:40.120 align:middle line:84%
encounters that for her were
highly negative involving

00:35:40.120 --> 00:35:45.309 align:middle line:84%
the devouring of babies and
terrible filth and terror.

00:35:45.309 --> 00:35:47.350 align:middle line:84%
And she said something at
the end of the session,

00:35:47.350 --> 00:35:50.330 align:middle line:84%
because she became much calmer
as we integrated some very

00:35:50.330 --> 00:35:52.090 align:middle line:90%
disturbing experiences.

00:35:52.090 --> 00:35:56.390 align:middle line:84%
She said, you think that if
we put out negative energy,

00:35:56.390 --> 00:35:59.160 align:middle line:84%
it attracts negative
experiences?

00:35:59.160 --> 00:36:00.670 align:middle line:90%
And that fit her very well.

00:36:00.670 --> 00:36:03.770 align:middle line:84%
Because she was a
person full of anger,

00:36:03.770 --> 00:36:05.131 align:middle line:90%
trying to move beyond anger.

00:36:05.131 --> 00:36:06.630 align:middle line:84%
And that's doesn't
mean this, again,

00:36:06.630 --> 00:36:08.490 align:middle line:84%
was a projection
of our own psyche.

00:36:08.490 --> 00:36:12.090 align:middle line:84%
But in some way,
the relationship,

00:36:12.090 --> 00:36:15.000 align:middle line:84%
the connection in
consciousness between her

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:16.954 align:middle line:84%
and whatever was coming
to her made sense.

00:36:16.954 --> 00:36:18.870 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it was
the kind of experiences

00:36:18.870 --> 00:36:20.520 align:middle line:90%
that you would expect.

00:36:20.520 --> 00:36:22.310 align:middle line:84%
I see Veronica as
somebody who would

00:36:22.310 --> 00:36:24.440 align:middle line:84%
be more likely to be
having experiences

00:36:24.440 --> 00:36:28.540 align:middle line:84%
of love and enlightenment
of a different kind.

00:36:28.540 --> 00:36:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And I think that may be
related, this is speculative,

00:36:31.460 --> 00:36:33.550 align:middle line:90%
of the energy that she puts out.

00:36:33.550 --> 00:36:36.950 align:middle line:84%
I know that Stan Grof
came here and is here

00:36:36.950 --> 00:36:39.020 align:middle line:90%
and I want to acknowledge Stan.

00:36:39.020 --> 00:36:42.300 align:middle line:84%
I always acknowledge this with
a little bit of mixed feelings.

00:36:42.300 --> 00:36:44.300 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:36:44.300 --> 00:36:47.546 align:middle line:90%


00:36:47.546 --> 00:36:50.220 align:middle line:84%
On the one hand, I'm
deeply grateful to him

00:36:50.220 --> 00:36:53.400 align:middle line:84%
because I learned about
nonordinary experiences

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:56.450 align:middle line:84%
as I never had before
during the training with him

00:36:56.450 --> 00:36:58.350 align:middle line:84%
and working with
him over the years.

00:36:58.350 --> 00:37:03.320 align:middle line:84%
The slight sort of
downward slope on this

00:37:03.320 --> 00:37:08.757 align:middle line:84%
is that he got me into this work
with the abduction phenomenon.

00:37:08.757 --> 00:37:10.840 align:middle line:84%
Because in the middle of
the training, for reasons

00:37:10.840 --> 00:37:13.490 align:middle line:84%
I've really never asked
him why he did this,

00:37:13.490 --> 00:37:17.630 align:middle line:84%
he handed me a paper in a book
on spiritual emergencies, which

00:37:17.630 --> 00:37:22.080 align:middle line:84%
was about the UFO
encounter phenomenon.

00:37:22.080 --> 00:37:25.340 align:middle line:84%
And I kept asking myself
after I read it, OK, this

00:37:25.340 --> 00:37:27.680 align:middle line:84%
is kind of Jungian
interpretation of it.

00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And I kept asking myself, yeah,
but is it really happening?

00:37:31.880 --> 00:37:33.070 align:middle line:90%
Is it real?

00:37:33.070 --> 00:37:38.887 align:middle line:84%
And within a few months I
began to see cases and sort

00:37:38.887 --> 00:37:40.860 align:middle line:90%
of totally changed my life.

00:37:40.860 --> 00:37:44.240 align:middle line:90%
And so for good or ill.

00:37:44.240 --> 00:37:47.200 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, thank you
in a way, Stan.

00:37:47.200 --> 00:37:50.290 align:middle line:90%


00:37:50.290 --> 00:37:53.700 align:middle line:84%
>>Dr. Mack, have
made any comparisons

00:37:53.700 --> 00:37:56.370 align:middle line:84%
between the
contactee experiences

00:37:56.370 --> 00:37:58.540 align:middle line:84%
and the ever increasing
number of those

00:37:58.540 --> 00:38:00.950 align:middle line:84%
that claim to be the victim
of some kind of mind control

00:38:00.950 --> 00:38:02.050 align:middle line:90%
technology?

00:38:02.050 --> 00:38:05.000 align:middle line:84%
>>That's another
frontier in this field.

00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:12.370 align:middle line:84%
Somebody did a study at
McCarthy in New Jersey.

00:38:12.370 --> 00:38:16.810 align:middle line:84%
Something like 40% of people
that are reporting mind control

00:38:16.810 --> 00:38:20.620 align:middle line:84%
experiments, when they were
studied in greater depth,

00:38:20.620 --> 00:38:23.280 align:middle line:90%
are abductees.

00:38:23.280 --> 00:38:28.220 align:middle line:84%
And there is a whole
complex of phenomenon

00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:30.950 align:middle line:84%
which seem to be
interrelated, which

00:38:30.950 --> 00:38:35.085 align:middle line:84%
