is that we are
learning something.

00:50:51.910 --> 00:50:53.280 align:middle line:90%
We are being told something.

00:50:53.280 --> 00:50:55.090 align:middle line:84%
We have been given
vital information

00:50:55.090 --> 00:50:57.510 align:middle line:84%
about what we're doing to
the earth, about what we're

00:50:57.510 --> 00:50:59.580 align:middle line:84%
doing to ourselves,
to one another,

00:50:59.580 --> 00:51:02.260 align:middle line:90%
and that it's a wake up.

00:51:02.260 --> 00:51:04.820 align:middle line:90%
It's an attempt to wake us up.

00:51:04.820 --> 00:51:07.490 align:middle line:90%
And we are aware of this trance.

00:51:07.490 --> 00:51:09.430 align:middle line:84%
I live with an
eight-year-old child.

00:51:09.430 --> 00:51:11.260 align:middle line:84%
So I get to see a lot
of children's movies

00:51:11.260 --> 00:51:13.560 align:middle line:84%
that I wouldn't probably
otherwise go to see.

00:51:13.560 --> 00:51:17.640 align:middle line:84%
So I went to see with him
"Rocky and Bullwinkle."

00:51:17.640 --> 00:51:20.460 align:middle line:84%
How many of you have seen
it, "Rocky and Bullwinkle."

00:51:20.460 --> 00:51:22.420 align:middle line:90%
Anyone at all?

00:51:22.420 --> 00:51:23.110 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't matter.

00:51:23.110 --> 00:51:27.750 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, what that's about is
that this fearless leader,

00:51:27.750 --> 00:51:30.070 align:middle line:84%
this bad guy, well he was
actually in a TV series

00:51:30.070 --> 00:51:33.310 align:middle line:84%
in the '60s as kind
of a Nazi character

00:51:33.310 --> 00:51:34.320 align:middle line:90%
called Fearless Leader.

00:51:34.320 --> 00:51:36.590 align:middle line:84%
And he's got to
Russian accomplices.

00:51:36.590 --> 00:51:39.290 align:middle line:84%
And he's taking over the
country and presumably the world

00:51:39.290 --> 00:51:42.950 align:middle line:90%
eventually through our RBTV.

00:51:42.950 --> 00:51:47.670 align:middle line:84%
Now RBTV is Really
Bad Television.

00:51:47.670 --> 00:51:52.640 align:middle line:84%
What he does is he broadcasts
nonstop these soporific

00:51:52.640 --> 00:51:53.240 align:middle line:90%
programs.

00:51:53.240 --> 00:51:56.440 align:middle line:84%
This sort of sterile
marketing of him

00:51:56.440 --> 00:52:01.247 align:middle line:84%
and all the empty products
and meaningless stuff,

00:52:01.247 --> 00:52:02.830 align:middle line:84%
which of course is
very much like what

00:52:02.830 --> 00:52:05.240 align:middle line:90%
we're getting for real now.

00:52:05.240 --> 00:52:08.381 align:middle line:84%
And everybody's kind
of like zombies.

00:52:08.381 --> 00:52:10.880 align:middle line:84%
They don't know what to do and
they're going to vote for him

00:52:10.880 --> 00:52:12.390 align:middle line:90%
and make him president.

00:52:12.390 --> 00:52:16.390 align:middle line:84%
So Bullwinkle, using
the latest technology,

00:52:16.390 --> 00:52:19.580 align:middle line:84%
gets sent by email
into the studio

00:52:19.580 --> 00:52:23.180 align:middle line:84%
and emerges from the
fax machine just in time

00:52:23.180 --> 00:52:25.890 align:middle line:84%
to break up the
television equipment.

00:52:25.890 --> 00:52:30.150 align:middle line:84%
And as he does so, blows up
the television equipment,

00:52:30.150 --> 00:52:34.044 align:middle line:84%
they can't hear Fearless
Leader's voice anymore.

00:52:34.044 --> 00:52:35.960 align:middle line:84%
And they all begin to
wake up from the trance.

00:52:35.960 --> 00:52:37.500 align:middle line:90%
You see them in the movie.

00:52:37.500 --> 00:52:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And then they begin to
think for themselves.

00:52:40.100 --> 00:52:44.470 align:middle line:84%
So somehow I see this
phenomenon as like that.

00:52:44.470 --> 00:52:45.440 align:middle line:90%
As a wake up.

00:52:45.440 --> 00:52:48.650 align:middle line:90%
Trying to get through to us.

00:52:48.650 --> 00:52:51.700 align:middle line:84%
We're cut off of through
this RBTV and the like

00:52:51.700 --> 00:52:55.440 align:middle line:84%
from our relationship with
the divine, with spirit.

00:52:55.440 --> 00:52:59.150 align:middle line:84%
And to get to us, because
we are so cut off,

00:52:59.150 --> 00:53:02.550 align:middle line:84%
it has to get to us in
a form we can recognize.

00:53:02.550 --> 00:53:04.630 align:middle line:84%
And this is why we
don't pay attention

00:53:04.630 --> 00:53:06.860 align:middle line:84%
to esoteric religion
like the Kabbalah

00:53:06.860 --> 00:53:12.110 align:middle line:84%
or all the Sufi truth or
even Seyyed Nasr's incredibly

00:53:12.110 --> 00:53:15.290 align:middle line:84%
eloquent words
because we are not

00:53:15.290 --> 00:53:18.740 align:middle line:84%
engaged in the practice
of knowing the divine.

00:53:18.740 --> 00:53:21.540 align:middle line:84%
So it has to take a
form we can recognize.

00:53:21.540 --> 00:53:25.122 align:middle line:84%
UFOs and spaceships
and this kind of thing.

00:53:25.122 --> 00:53:26.205 align:middle line:90%
Not that they're not real.

00:53:26.205 --> 00:53:28.509 align:middle line:84%
They've been around
for centuries.

00:53:28.509 --> 00:53:30.050 align:middle line:84%
There's pictures
from the Renaissance

00:53:30.050 --> 00:53:33.810 align:middle line:84%
which shows UFOs in
Renaissance paintings.

00:53:33.810 --> 00:53:36.090 align:middle line:84%
But it's hard to interpret
some of these things.

00:53:36.090 --> 00:53:39.130 align:middle line:84%
But it's now that
phenomena like this

00:53:39.130 --> 00:53:43.230 align:middle line:84%
are coming to us as
if a kind of return

00:53:43.230 --> 00:53:45.930 align:middle line:84%
of the repressed from the
cosmos through the spiritually

00:53:45.930 --> 00:53:46.610 align:middle line:90%
impaired.

00:53:46.610 --> 00:53:49.480 align:middle line:90%
It's a crashing through.

00:53:49.480 --> 00:53:57.190 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the experiences
are receiving this information

00:53:57.190 --> 00:54:00.950 align:middle line:84%
like in this way that is so
profoundly transformative,

00:54:00.950 --> 00:54:02.540 align:middle line:90%
as Veronica was talking about.

00:54:02.540 --> 00:54:07.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's the most
important aspect of it.

00:54:07.130 --> 00:54:12.470 align:middle line:84%
And this is the thing I wanted
to really emphasize and close

00:54:12.470 --> 00:54:18.950 align:middle line:84%
with is that we have
work to do in developing

00:54:18.950 --> 00:54:22.517 align:middle line:84%
a reliable epistemology
methodology science, whatever

00:54:22.517 --> 00:54:23.350 align:middle line:90%
you want to call it.

00:54:23.350 --> 00:54:24.760 align:middle line:90%
A way of knowing.

00:54:24.760 --> 00:54:26.560 align:middle line:84%
Because knowing was
originally a sacred act

00:54:26.560 --> 00:54:27.570 align:middle line:90%
for knowing the divine.

00:54:27.570 --> 00:54:30.610 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't just about breaking
up pieces of the material world

00:54:30.610 --> 00:54:32.110 align:middle line:84%
and then studying
them in isolation.

00:54:32.110 --> 00:54:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Knowing was about opening
consciousness, soul to who

00:54:35.820 --> 00:54:38.710 align:middle line:90%
we were in a much larger sense.

00:54:38.710 --> 00:54:40.070 align:middle line:90%
And we've lost that.

00:54:40.070 --> 00:54:44.210 align:middle line:84%
So in a way, what I think
this is helping us to do

00:54:44.210 --> 00:54:48.220 align:middle line:84%
is force me to do is
to work on developing

00:54:48.220 --> 00:54:52.090 align:middle line:84%
a sacred science or an
epistemology of the divine

00:54:52.090 --> 00:54:54.200 align:middle line:90%
or whatever it would be.

00:54:54.200 --> 00:54:58.900 align:middle line:84%
So we can begin to legitimate
this kind of a report.

00:54:58.900 --> 00:55:01.620 align:middle line:84%
Which tends to get
rejected and ridiculed

00:55:01.620 --> 00:55:04.120 align:middle line:84%
for all kinds of reasons,
because it is threatening,

00:55:04.120 --> 00:55:05.770 align:middle line:90%
and all the reasons you know.

00:55:05.770 --> 00:55:08.260 align:middle line:84%
But there is also
the valid critique

00:55:08.260 --> 00:55:10.420 align:middle line:84%
which is that we
haven't developed

00:55:10.420 --> 00:55:16.280 align:middle line:84%
a reliable, systematic way
of knowing and understanding

00:55:16.280 --> 00:55:21.540 align:middle line:84%
these realms from which we
have so separated ourselves.

00:55:21.540 --> 00:55:22.580 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:55:22.580 --> 00:55:26.230 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

